# HTTP response headers for a header-capable host (Cloudflare Pages / Netlify).
#
# GitHub Pages CANNOT set real HTTP headers, so this file is INERT there (served
# as a plain file). It activates automatically when the site is deployed on
# Cloudflare Pages or Netlify — see docs/HOSTING_MIGRATION.md. These values are
# the OWASP 2026 baseline and target an A+ on securityheaders.com / MDN Observatory.

/*
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; font-src 'self'; img-src 'self' data:; connect-src 'self' https://rxnav.nlm.nih.gov https://api.fda.gov https://data.medicaid.gov https://clinicaltables.nlm.nih.gov https://openrx-api.onrender.com; base-uri 'none'; object-src 'none'; form-action 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'; upgrade-insecure-requests
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(), camera=(), microphone=(), payment=(), usb=(), interest-cohort=()
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: same-origin
  X-Permitted-Cross-Domain-Policies: none

# form-action is 'self', not 'none': the header search on every non-home page is a
# real GET form to "/". A meta CSP and a header CSP are enforced INDEPENDENTLY —
# a form must pass BOTH — so leaving 'none' here would silently kill that search
# the moment this file goes live on a header-capable host. 'self' still blocks the
# threat form-action exists for: an injected form posting to a third-party origin.

# Long-cache the fingerprint-free static assets (safe: content-addressed by path).
/assets/fonts/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

# Note: add `; preload` to Strict-Transport-Security ONLY after every subdomain
# is HTTPS and you have committed to https://hstspreload.org submission (it is a
# hard-to-reverse, browser-baked commitment).
